{EVENTS HELD IN MEMORIAL HALL}
New Year's Eve party. W.I. party in January. Several fund raising dances + Halloween and Christmas Discos for children. 2 Ceilidhs each year. County Council & General Election polling station. Memorabilia exhibition covering village life and including exhibits from the Stone Age. W.I. Safari Supper each year uses Hall as base. Summer Playscheme each year. Treasure Hunt around village from Hall each year. Annual barbeque. N.F.U. Dinner Dance. Sale for the blind held annually. Wedding receptions also take place in the Hall.
The Hall was built in 1957 followed by the opening of the Supper Room extension in 1981
